Location: North Carolina



Getting job at Vanguard Charlotte Office?


Quote


Postby kingjimmy » Sat Sep 07, 2013 9:59 pm 
HelloI didn't realize it until today, but I recently discovered that Vanguard has a corporate office here in Charlotte, NC, where I live. I'm already involved in the banking world and work as a mortgage underwriter. Honestly I feel my particular niche in the underwriting world only has about 5-10 years left as far as job security, as my position is very specialized and highly dependent on the winds that blow in Washington. I highly enjoy issues related to personal finance and of late have been thinking of ways I might eventually move out of my current job into something else. I very much buy into the investment philosophy of Jack Bogle, having read several Boglehead books, and think that a career at Vanguard could be something I enjoy. I'm very analytical and am a people person. I have a couple years experience in underwriting, and have had to appear in court hundreds of times on behalf of my bank to represent the bank in foreclosure matters.With that said, is anybody here on the forum aware of the type of positions that are typically available at the Charlotte office? How many people work there? What's the corporate culture like? How does one get their foot in the door, and what's the pay like? What does Vanguard usually look for in new employees?Any insights would be appreciated.ThanksJimmy
Jimmy | http://www.bigbadbanker.com


