Re: Getting job at Vanguard Charlotte Office?


Quote


Postby LadyGeek » Sun Sep 08, 2013 9:52 am 
This thread is now in the Personal Finance (Not Investing) forum (employment).Your prior career choice thread: Get an MBA or Invest?I would assume that working for Vanguard is no different than any other Investment management company. The job might be great, but you don't get along with your manager. Or, the job might not turn out to what you thought you'd be doing.In any case, I want to point out that while this forum promotes Vanguard as a low-cost investment choice, there is no connection to the company itself. If Schwab or Fidelity was cheaper, we'd be promoting those companies (which we do, when appropriate).Your best chance of finding out about Vanguard employment is to ask them directly.
 To some, the glass is half full. To others, the glass is half empty. To an engineer, it's twice the size it needs to be.


