nisiprius 
Advisory Board
Posts: 33629 Joined: Thu Jul 26, 2007 9:33 am
Location: The terrestrial, globular, planetary hunk of matter, flattened at the poles, is my abode.--O. Henry



Re: Getting job at Vanguard Charlotte Office?


Quote


Postby nisiprius » Sun Sep 08, 2013 10:32 am 
Vanguard mutual funds are individual business companies, and some of those companies have "Charlotte" in the name. Indeed, the new International Bond Index Fund is one of them. From the Statement of Additional Information:"Vanguard Charlotte Funds (the Trust) currently offers the following fund and share classes (identified by ticker symbol)..."I have no idea whether this fund has any particular connection with the Charlotte office, or whether it's just something they picked as an apropos name. But anyway, if nothing else, it's something you can ask about at the job interview in order to put up a show of having tried to find out about the company.

					Last edited by nisiprius on Sun Sep 08, 2013 10:40 am, edited 1 time in total.
									
Annual income twenty pounds, annual expenditure nineteen nineteen and six, result happiness; Annual income twenty pounds, annual expenditure twenty pounds ought and six, result misery.


