Top








 
BrandonBogle 
Posts: 1879 Joined: Mon Jan 28, 2013 11:19 pm



Re: Getting job at Vanguard Charlotte Office?


Quote


Postby BrandonBogle » Sun Sep 08, 2013 10:44 am 
JamesSFO wrote:I know my CFP and flagship advisor are all in that office so they have a team of those there.I also met someone from that team/division/area a couple years ago. Very sweet guy. I was friends with his wife from my work. He had positive experiences to say and was happy to hear I already was a Vanguard client. But as with most any job, your direct manager setting your responsibilities and your division manager setting policy and goals will make all the difference in the world. As others have suggested, it could be a good talking point in the interview to asks about the corporate culture with how Vanguard is structured. I'll bet it's likely very different than the megabank culture.As a side note, depending on which niche area of mortgage underwriting you are in, Teachers aka TIAA-Cref has recently been looking for portfolio analysts in their lending group.


Top








 
dandan14 
Posts: 924 Joined: Wed Feb 11, 2009 7:32 am



Re: Getting job at Vanguard Charlotte Office?


Quote


Postby dandan14 » Sun Sep 08, 2013 2:39 pm 
I've investigated this path as well.  I've talked with several vanguard employees (thanks linkedin) in both Charlotte and Valley Forge.  It seems that they really like to hire from within and do most of their hiring for the phone support positions.  If you want to do that for a while and gain some great experience, it would likely be a fun job.  According to my friend who works in the Charlotte office, phone reps start at about 45k.


